Data: National Health and Nutrition Examination Survey https://wwwn.cdc.gov/nchs/nhanes/continuousnhanes/default.aspx?cycle=2017-2020

The National Health and Nutrition Examination Survey (NHANES) is a program of studies designed to assess the health and nutritional status of adults and children in the United States. The survey is unique in that it combines interviews and physical examinations.

The NHANES program began in the early 1960s and has been conducted as a series of surveys focusing on different population groups or health topics. In 1999, the survey became a continuous program that has a changing focus on a variety of health and nutrition measurements to meet emerging needs. The survey examines a nationally representative sample of about 5,000 persons each year. These persons are located in counties across the country, 15 of which are visited each year.

The NHANES interview includes demographic, socioeconomic, dietary, and health-related questions. The examination component consists of medical, dental, and physiological measurements, as well as laboratory tests administered by highly trained medical personnel.

We chose the dataset that is from 2017 to 2020

BodyMeasures = read.xport("P_BMX.XPT")
BodyMeasures
NA
# age <18, BMI
BMIC = BodyMeasures %>%
  dplyr::mutate(BMI = BMDBMIC) %>% 
  dplyr::rename(Weight = BMXWT) %>%
  dplyr::select(SEQN,BMI,Weight) %>%
  tidyr::drop_na()
BMIC  
# age > 18, BMI
BMIA = BodyMeasures %>% 
  dplyr::filter(is.na(BMDBMIC)) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(BMI = ifelse( BMXBMI < 18.5,1,
               ifelse( BMXBMI >= 18.5 & BMXBMI < 25,2,
               ifelse( BMXBMI >= 25 & BMXBMI < 35, 3,
               ifelse( BMXBMI >= 35,4,NA))))) %>%
  dplyr::rename(Weight = BMXWT) %>%
  dplyr::select(SEQN,BMI,Weight) %>%
  tidyr::drop_na()
BMIA
# combine children BMI and adult BMI two dataframes
BMI = rbind(BMIA,BMIC)
BMI 
Demographics = read.xport("P_DEMO.XPT")
Demographics
# filter a few data which is refused and don't know
Demographics = Demographics %>%
  dplyr::filter(DMDBORN4 != 77, #77 = refused
         DMDBORN4 != 99, #99 = don't know
         DMDEDUC2 != 7,  # 7= refused
         DMDEDUC2 != 9,  # 9 = don't know
         DMDMARTZ != 77,
         DMDMARTZ != 99) %>%
  dplyr::rename(Gender = RIAGENDR,
                Age = RIDAGEYR,
                Race = RIDRETH3,
                Country_of_Birth = DMDBORN4,
                Education = DMDEDUC2,
                Marital = DMDMARTZ) %>%
  dplyr::select(SEQN,Gender,Age,Race,Country_of_Birth,Education,Marital)

         Food_shopper = DBQ940,
         Share_food_shopping = DBQ945) 
Q_Diet
# filter out "don't know" and "refused"
Q_Diet = Q_Diet %>%
  filter(Milk != 9,
         FastFood != 7777,
         FastFood != 9999,
         Food_From_Grocery != 9999,
         FrozenMeals != 9999,
         Heard_of_My_Plate != 9,

  # 22 = more than 21 meals per week
  mutate(FastFood = replace(FastFood, FastFood == 5555, 22)) %>% 
  # 91 = More than 90 times in 30 days
  mutate(Food_From_Grocery = replace(Food_From_Grocery, Food_From_Grocery == 6666, 91)) %>%
  # 91 = More than 90 times in 30 days
  mutate(FrozenMeals = replace(FrozenMeals, FrozenMeals == 6666, 91))

# Read the fasting data
Fasting = read.xport("P_FASTQX.XPT")
Fasting

Fasting_s = Fasting %>%
               # 2 =  didn't have coffee or tea with cream or sugar during fasting
  dplyr::filter(PHQ020 == 2, 
                # didn't use alcohol during fasting
                PHQ030 == 2,
                # didn't use gum, mints, lozenges or cough drops during fasting
                PHQ040 == 2,
                # didn't use antacids, laxatives, or anti-diarrheals during fasting
                PHQ050 == 2,
                # didn't use dietary supplements
                PHQ060 ==2)%>%
  dplyr::rename(Fast_hour = PHAFSTHR,
         Fast_min = PHAFSTMN) %>%
  dplyr::select(SEQN, Fast_hour, Fast_min)


Fasting_s
# combine fasting hours and minutes
Fasting_s$Fast_hour = Fasting_s$Fast_hour + Fasting_s$Fast_min/60

Fasting_s = Fasting_s %>% 
  dplyr::filter(Fast_hour >= 10) %>%
  dplyr::select(-Fast_min)

Fasting_s

# read Diabetes dataset
Q_Diabetes= read.xport("P_DIQ.XPT")
Q_Diabetes
Q_Diabetes = Q_Diabetes %>%
                           # 1 = have been told that have diabetes,
  dplyr::mutate(Diabetes = ifelse(DIQ010 == 1,1,
                    # 0 = never been told that have diabetes
                    ifelse(DIQ010 == 2,0,
                    # 0.5 = have been told that have prediabetes,
                    ifelse(DIQ010 == 3,0.5,NA)))) %>%
  dplyr::select(SEQN,Diabetes) 
  
Diabetes_Glucose_Insulin = merge(Q_Diabetes,Glucose_Insulin)
# filter out participants who have been told that have diabetes.
# because these participants take medicines that impact blood glucose and insulin level.
Diabetes1 = Diabetes_Glucose_Insulin %>% dplyr::filter(Diabetes == 1)
Diabetes0 = Diabetes_Glucose_Insulin %>% dplyr::filter(Diabetes != 1) 
Diabetes0 = Diabetes0 %>%
  dplyr::select(-Diabetes) %>%
  # 0 = normal, 0.5 = prediabetes, 1 = diabetes
  dplyr::mutate(Diabetes = ifelse(Fasting_glucose < 100, 0,
                    ifelse(Fasting_glucose >=100 & Fasting_glucose <126, 0.5,
                    ifelse(Fasting_glucose >= 126,1,NA))))

Diabetes_BMI = merge(Diabetes0,BMI)
cor(Diabetes_BMI, method = "spearman")
